To fully test the paid flow, you'll need to:
Sign up on the live site
Generate a CV
Click "Unlock for $10" → Stripe checkout
Use test card 4242 4242 4242 4242 (if in test mode) or real card (live mode)

1. Paste background → Generate CV
2. Paste job → Analyze Job (inline)
3. Both exist → "Analyze Match" appears in sidebar
4. Match complete → Click "Cover Letter" to generate
5. Toggle between CV and Cover Letter

These are official Claude Code plugins you've enabled. Each adds specialized capabilities:
Plugin	What it does
frontend-design	High-quality UI/component generation
github	GitHub integration (PRs, issues, etc.)
feature-dev	Guided feature development workflow
supabase	Supabase MCP tools (DB, auth, etc.)
security-guidance	Security best practices
stripe	Stripe integration helpers, test cards
They come from Anthropic's official plugin repo (@claude-plugins-official). You can invoke their skills with /plugin-name:skill (e.g., /stripe:test-cards).
Official plugins that add extra skills:
frontend-design — Better UI generation
github — PR/issue tools
feature-dev — Guided dev workflow
supabase — Database tools
security-guidance — Security tips
stripe — Payment helpers


